Project Overview
You have been hired as a junior front-end developer to create a landing page for a fictional streetwear brand, UrbanFit Apparel. The page should be modern, stylish, and responsive, reflecting the brand’s identity.

Project Requirements


✅ Header

Company logo (UrbanFit Apparel)
Navigation menu: Home | Shop | About | Contact


✅ Hero Section

Full-width background image of a model wearing UrbanFit’s latest collection
Headline: "Style Meets Comfort"
Subheadline: "Explore the latest trends in streetwear fashion."
Call-to-action (CTA) button: "Shop Now"


✅ About Section

Short paragraph introducing UrbanFit:
"UrbanFit Apparel is a streetwear brand that blends style and function, creating high-quality clothing for the modern urban lifestyle."


✅ Featured Products Section

Display 3-4 best-selling items with images, names, and prices
Example:
Oversized Hoodie – $59.99
Streetwear Joggers – $49.99
Graphic Tee – $29.99


✅ Customer Reviews Section

Display 2-3 testimonials from happy customers
Example:
"Best hoodie I’ve ever owned! Super comfy and stylish." – Alex R.


✅ Newsletter Signup Section

Headline: "Stay Ahead of the Trends"
Short text: "Join our newsletter for exclusive drops and discounts."
Email input field + “Subscribe” button


✅ Footer

Social media icons (Instagram, TikTok, Twitter)
Copyright info (© 2025 UrbanFit Apparel. All rights reserved.)


Bonus Features (Optional)

✨ Hover effects on buttons and images
✨ Smooth scrolling for navigation links
✨ CSS animations (e.g., fade-in effects on sections)
✨ Responsive design (works on mobile & desktop)